============================================
Readme / documentation for the execo package
============================================

The execo python module offers a high level API for parallel local or
remote processes execution with the Action class hierarchy, and a
lower level API with the Process class, for handling individual
subprocesses.

The additional execo_g5k python module provides a set of tools and
extensions to execo, to be used in Grid5000

installation instructions
=========================

links
-----

execo package download: http://graal.ens-lyon.fr/~mimbert/execo/execo-1.1.tar.gz

execo code repository: http://graal.ens-lyon.fr/~mimbert/execo/execo.git

execo documentation:
http://graal.ens-lyon.fr/~mimbert/execo/doc/index.html 
http://graal.ens-lyon.fr/~mimbert/execo/doc/epydoc/index.html

prerequisites
-------------

execo installation requires python (>= 2.5) and make (for debian 5.x,
packages python, make)

to build the documentation, sphinx is needed (for debian
5.x, packages python-sphinx)

installation
------------

use the supplied makefile.

main targets are:

- build: to compile py files.

- install: to install. Pass option PREFIX=... for installing in a
  non-default location (default PREFIX is /usr/local).

- doc: to build doc

- check: to run unittests and doctests

- clean: to clean everything

- dist: to create the execo package in dist/

- epydoc: another generated documentation (requires python-epydoc
  package)

usage
=====

See html documentation for module execo and execo_g5k at
http://graal.ens-lyon.fr/~mimbert/execo/doc/index.html
